For the specific goals of this analysis, we are interested in how the terms of this equation change as a result of fire-induced forest loss. Following Duveiller et al.2, we make the assumption that fire-induced forest loss is too small to generate strong feedbacks in the cloud regime, and as a consequence we assume ∆εcloud = 0 and ∆Tcloud = 0 (i.e., no change in cloud emissivity and temperature). Therefore, the change in sensible and ground heat fluxes (∆(H + G) under clear sky conditions can be calculated by rearranging Eqs. 1 and 2:4\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
